I am now using vi for everyday work, but has to use my poor emacs shortcut skills to do bash command insertion. So here I am now trying to expore how to use vim with bash.

http://www.jukie.net/bart/blog/20040326082602


add this to .bashrc

	 set -o vi
         # ^l clear screen
         bind -m vi-insert "\C-l":clear-screen
#Working Productively in Bash's Vi Command Line Editing Mode (with Cheat Sheet)
